---
// TheGap.astro — AesCode Co. v2.0
// Asymmetric 4/8 editorial grid — The structural problem AesCode solves
---

<section class="gap-section section-primary bg-surface-low" id="the-problem" aria-labelledby="gap-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="gap-section__grid grid-12">

      <!-- Left: Section label + headline (4 cols) -->
      <div class="col-4 gap-section__left">
        <p class="label-sm mb-lg reveal" style="color: var(--accent);">THE PROBLEM</p>
        <h2 id="gap-heading" class="display-md serif italic text-primary reveal reveal--delay-1">
          The gap is not ambition. It is infrastructure.
        </h2>
        <div class="hairline hairline--accent hairline--short mt-xl reveal reveal--delay-2"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Content (8 cols) -->
      <div class="col-8 gap-section__right">
        <!-- Key stat -->
        <div class="gap-section__stat reveal">
          <div class="gap-section__stat-number">
            <span class="data-lg mono text-accent" data-counter data-target="834" data-suffix="M">834M</span>
            <span class="gap-section__stat-label label-md">ABHA digital health IDs registered</span>
          </div>
          <p class="body-sm text-muted gap-section__stat-note">
            National Digital Health Mission, Government of India, 2025
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Body copy -->
        <div class="gap-section__body reveal reveal--delay-1">
          <p class="body-lg serif text-on-surface mb-xl" style="color: var(--on-surface);">
            India has 834 million ABHA digital health IDs and 438,000 registered health facilities. The data infrastructure exists. The engineering talent exists. Clinical AI adoption is blocked by one thing: trust.
          </p>
          <p class="body-md mb-xl" style="color: var(--on-surface-variant);">
            Hospital procurement teams will not deploy software that has not been independently validated against Indian patient populations. AI trained on US or European datasets performs differently — sometimes dangerously differently — on Indian patients. And there is no Indian institution that benchmarks and certifies clinical AI tools.
          </p>
          <p class="body-md semibold text-primary">
            Aescode builds that institution.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .gap-section__grid {
    column-gap: var(--space-4xl);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .gap-section__left {
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(68px + var(--space-2xl));
  }

  .gap-section__stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-xl);
    background: var(--surface-container-lowest);
    border: 0.5px solid rgba(196, 198, 206, 0.4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }
  .gap-section__stat-number {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .gap-section__stat-label {
    color: var(--secondary);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .gap-section__stat-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--outline);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--data-sm);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .gap-section__body { max-width: 100%; }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .gap-section__grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2xl); }
    .gap-section__left { position: static; }
  }
</style>
